Weâre thrilled to announce Reflex (formerly Pynecone - more on that in a bit!) and the $5 million we raised in seed funding led by Lux Capital with participation from Abstract Ventures , Box Group , Y Combinator , Picus Capital , and Outset Capital . Additionally, we are thrilled to bring on some fantastic founders as angel investors, including Qasar Younis (Cofounder and CEO of Applied Intuition), Jack Altman (Cofounder and CEO of Lattice), Paul Copplestone (Cofounder and CEO of Supabase), Matt Kraning (CTO, Cortex at Palo Alto Networks), Alfredo Andere (Cofounder and CEO of Latch Bio), and With this investment, we will accelerate the development of our ecosystem and release our hosting service optimized for usability and This will allow our users to build powerful Reflex apps in minutes and deploy them with a single Why we started Reflex Web apps are the most common way for developers to share their But even for skilled engineers, without experience in traditional frontend tools like Javascript or React, making a web app can be overwhelming and And once their app is created, deploying it is often a Over the years, many and frameworks have tried to make web development more accessible, but they all have limitations and graduation risks compared to standard web With Reflex, we have created a framework that lets developers leverage their existing Python skills to build and deploy apps without compromising on flexibility or Reflex allows you to make anything from a small data science project to a , web Since Reflex apps compile down to traditional frontend frameworks, there s no constraint on the type of apps you can Instead of reinventing the web development ecosystem, we re trying to make the existing ecosystem more What Weâve Done So Far Since our launch in December , our community has grown to 5,000 monthly developers making ,000 Reflex apps, + contributors to our GitHub project, and over 1,500 members in our We ve also seen a broad range of skill levels and use cases, from software engineers at large companies building internal apps to startups building their main And itâs not just tech companies: Reflex is used in a wide range of industries ranging from biology and quant finance to As Pynecone, we participated in Y Combinatorâs Winter cohort with the goal of making an framework for web apps in pure We formally rebranded from Pynecone to Reflex to align with our goal of creating a platform that is intuitive and simple to learn, yet flexible and robust enough to handle any use As we grow, our mission is to make our platform the easiest way to build and deploy web Next Steps We have three core goals for the next stage of our Reflex Hosting: The project is only half of the In the upcoming months, we will build and release a beta of our hosting service so users can quickly deploy, scale, and share their Our primary areas of focus for our hosting service are security, reliability, and optimizing app performance by running our app close to the user on the Rapid Onboarding: Our goal is to be the easiest way to build web We re working on adding base app templates, components, and styles so developers can go from an idea to a working app as fast as Core Framework: We will continue to grow our framework to have feature parity with traditional This includes adding more complex styling methods like detailed animations and improvements to our core component A more detailed roadmap of whatâs coming next can be found here . Photovoltaic (PV) technologies and solar inverters are not known to pose any significant health dangers to their The most important dangers posed are increased highway traffic during the relatively short construction period and dangers posed to trespassers of contact with high voltage This latter risk is mitigated by signage and the security measures that the industry uses to deter Source: North Carolina State University How does a solar farm affect the land s permeability? Solar farms maintain the permeable nature of the land because they involve limited concrete use only for inverter and transformer pads, preserving the ability of the soil to absorb How is the land s vegetation managed during the solar farm s lifetime? The land is seeded with native grasses, and the vegetation is actively maintained during the project s After deconstruction, it is Does the solar farm impact agricultural land productivity? While the solar farm operates, the agricultural land typically lies fallow, allowing the soil to naturally What is the estimated useful life of a project? Bringing Stelo safety to more places Home Careers API Docs Download Feb , Making web3 safe and easy to understand Today we’re announcing three new products to help us accomplish our goal of making all crypto transactions safe and easy to Stelo We’ve redesigned the Stelo extension from scratch to make it simpler, faster, and easier to You can download it here . Stelo for We’re releasing our developer API to empower every dApp and wallet to use the Stelo Transaction Engine that powers the Stelo We’re launching , a token approvals experience to understand your wallet health and keep it We’re also announcing a $6m fundraise led by a16z Read on for more about our vision for a safer, more user friendly crypto Why Stelo Imagine a world where every time you went to buy a cup of coffee there was a small chance all of your money was So you have three wallets - one for coffee, one for shopping, and one you keep locked in your parents This is the state of crypto in At Stelo, we’re here to fix We’re building the user interface to web3 so that people can have the confidence to be at the center of their digital lives without the fear of losing We launched the Stelo extension in September to protect people from scams and Since then, we’ve protected thousands of wallets holding assets worth over $100m. The core of all of our products is the Stelo Transaction It does three things: Simulation - simulates the transaction and lets you know what assets are leaving and entering your Enrichment - enriches the transaction with on and data such as human readable names, recognizable NFTs, and Risk analysis - analyzes the transaction and surfaces risk factors to help prevent you from getting phished or Stelo Extension v2 One of the most powerful aspects of web3 is that any developer can build a website that interacts with any Developers don’t have to ask permission to interact with Uniswap pools or utilize OpenSea’s marketplace However, one of the risks of decentralization is that websites can tell you they’re doing one thing and actually construct a transaction that does something The source of truth needs to live outside of the The Stelo extension secures every transaction and acts like a firewall for your It translates complex transactions and signatures into plain English so you can transact with Here’s an example: Safe transaction in Stelo (left) MetaMask (right). Transactions are only one half of the signatures have become an increasingly common way to save users gas fees for actions such as granting approvals to DEXs, listing NFTs on marketplaces, and interacting with multisig contracts like a Gnosis However, wallets have very little understanding of signatures, which leaves users blind to the potentially catastrophic effects of signing these The recent Kevin Rose attack utilized this dynamic to trick him into signing away over $2m worth of his NFTs in a single Stelo interprets the most popular signature types and runs them through the Stelo Transaction The result is safe, signatures that people can feel more confident For example, here’s what Kevin saw in Stelo what he would have seen in What Kevin Rose would have seen in Stelo (left) what he saw in MetaMask (right). Chrome extensions can be a dangerous attack vector in and of themselves so we’ve gone through many steps to be as transparent and secure as Stelo never has access to your seed phrase or private keys and the extension has been fully open source since day Stelo for Developers Since we launched the first version of Stelo, developers have been reaching out to bring Stelo intelligence to their own dApps and Our goal at Stelo is to make every transaction safe and easy to understand, whether users have Stelo installed or Today we’re announcing two products for developers - Stelo API and Stelo Stelo API enables transaction safety for every dApp and It brings the same transaction intelligence and risk analysis that powers the Stelo extension to any Developers will have everything they need to bring their users context, understanding, and You can read more about the API at or reach out to us to get an API Stelo Embed allows any dApp or wallet connection product to embed a Stelo transaction screen on their site — think of it like a trusted checkout screen for your dApp that can increase confidence and conversion Embed can be implemented in a matter of minutes and gives you all the benefits of the Stelo API without the development Developers just pass the same transaction object they send to the wallet and Stelo Embed takes care of the You can preview Stelo Embed in action on our new token approvals site – . One of the biggest risk vectors in web3 is open Many of the most used contracts, from OpenSea to Uniswap, rely on token Approvals are permissions to move your assets and are required for token swaps and NFT In order to provide the simplest user experience with the fewest transactions, these dApps request indefinite approval to move users While this reduces friction, it a
